`crates/ctx-cage/src/` is the sandboxing crate's core: it builds bwrap-based cage sessions, brokers tool calls and API egress across the sandbox boundary, and runs the prepareā†’runā†’teardown lifecycle for one invocation. Depending on this crate gets you `lifecycle::execute`, `cli::resolve_mode`, and the `bwrap`/`proxy`/`protocol` types; construction of bwrap argv, wire frames, and proxy header rewriting all stay internal to their submodules.

The crate is organized around three seams that must move together: `protocol.rs` defines the length-prefixed frame format used by both `bin/ctx_cage_client.rs` (client side) and `broker.rs` (host side, via `serve_one`/`run`) ā€” a frame change requires updating both. `bwrap/` defines the mount-layout constants (`ADR-046` target_root binding, `ADR-049` resolv.conf stub) that `lifecycle/` and `runtime.rs` both depend on for path agreement ā€” `runtime.rs`'s `synth_claude_config` keys its trust map on the same canonicalized `target_root` path that `bwrap` binds identically in-cage. `proxy.rs`/`proxy/head.rs` is the sole egress path bound into the cage at `/run/ctx/api.sock`; its `ProxyConfig.api_key` Some/None branch (inject real key vs. pass through client's own) is the single place the "own API key vs. subscription OAuth" distinction is enforced, and `runtime.rs` assumes the proxy is listening at `CAGE_BASE_URL` for OAuth-mode launches.

Crate-spanning invariants: the real API key/credential never crosses into the cage except via the proxy (never mounted, never in env); `target_root` must be canonicalized before any bwrap bind or trust-map key is derived from it; `spawn.rs`'s `Spawner` trait is the only way `broker.rs` executes allowlisted tools, keeping subprocess creation centralized; `error.rs`'s `CageError` is the crate-wide error type, with richer detail expected to live on module-local Result types rather than growing new `CageError` variants. `lib.rs` documents but doesn't enforce the read-write-workspace-only / no-`$HOME` / `no_new_privs`-without-seccomp posture ā€” enforcement lives in `bwrap/` and `lifecycle/`.

`cli.rs` resolves CLI flags to a `Mode` and gates billed modes on `allow_spend`; `summarize.rs` and `runtime.rs` are auxiliary, independent concerns (post-run leaf-summary refresh and claude-runtime credential synthesis) that don't interact with the sandbox-construction seam directly.